-- California May Have Deal to Close Budget Deficit, Schwarzenegger Aide Says
-- B y   M i c h a e l   M a r o i s   a n d   C h r i s t o p h e r   P a l m e r i
-- 2010-09-23T23:03:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/california-may-have-deal-to-close-budget-deficit-schwarzenegger-aide-says.html
California Governor Arnold
Schwarzenegger and lawmakers may have reached a deal to close a
$19 billion budget deficit, the governor’s spokesman said.  “It looks like we have a deal,” the spokesman, Aaron
McLear, said outside the governor’s private office in Santa
Monica.  To contact the reporter on this story:
